main-text.text: 6.1 Personal precautions, protective equipment and emergency procedures
main-text.name: section_header

main-text.text: Wear respiratory protection. Avoid dust formation. Avoid breathing vapors, mist or gas. Ensure adequate ventilation. Evacuate personnel to safe areas. Avoid breathing dust.
main-text.name: text

main-text.text: Prevent further leakage or spillage if safe to do so. Do not let product enter drains.
main-text.name: text

main-text.text: 6.3 Methods and materials for containment and cleaning up
main-text.name: section_header

main-text.text: Pick up and arrange disposal without creating dust. Sweep up and shovel. Keep in suitable, closed containers for disposal.
main-text.name: text

main-text.text: Avoid contact with skin and eyes. Avoid formation of dust and aerosols.Avoid exposure - obtain special instructions before use.
main-text.name: text

main-text.text: Provide appropriate exhaust ventilation at places where dust is formed.
main-text.name: text

main-text.text: 7.2 Conditions for safe storage, including any incompatibilities
main-text.name: section_header

main-text.text: Store in cool place. Keep container tightly closed in a dry and well-ventilated place.
main-text.name: text

main-text.text: Avoid contact with skin, eyes and clothing. Wash hands before breaks and immediately after handling the product.
main-text.name: text

main-text.text: Face shield and safety glasses Use equipment for eye protection tested and approved under appropriate government standards such as NIOSH (US) or EN 166(EU).
main-text.name: text

main-text.text: Handle with gloves. Gloves must be inspected prior to use. Use proper glove removal technique (without touching glove's outer surface) to avoid skin contact with this product. Dispose of contaminated gloves after use in accordance with applicable laws and good laboratory practices. Wash and dry hands.
main-text.name: text

main-text.text: The selected protective gloves have to satisfy the specifications of EU Directive 89/686/EEC and the standard EN 374 derived from it.
main-text.name: text

main-text.text: Material: Nitrile rubber Minimum layer thickness: 0,11 mm Break through time: 480 min Material tested:Dermatril® (KCL 740 / Aldrich Z677272, Size M)

main-text.text: If used in solution, or mixed with other substances, and under conditions which differ from EN 374, contact the supplier of the CE approved gloves. It should not be construed as offering an approval for any specific use scenario.
main-text.name: text

main-text.text: Complete suit protecting against chemicals, The type of protective equipment must be selected according to the concentration and amount of the dangerous substance at the specific workplace.
main-text.name: text

main-text.text: Where risk assessment shows air-purifying respirators are appropriate use a full-face particle respirator type N100 (US) or type P3 (EN 143) respirator cartridges as a backup to engineering controls. If the respirator is the sole means of protection, use a full-face supplied air respirator. Use respirators and components tested and approved under appropriate government standards such as NIOSH (US) or CEN (EU).
